{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17488640","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17488640"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:50:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:50:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"499"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"499","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/499"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.01,0.01,0.5,0.46]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"499"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86587"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"499","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/499"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"499"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70869"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"433"},{"type":"tags","id":"4963"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9022"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11636"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1166"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2698"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28466"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40682"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43961"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86587","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/86587"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 73-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with 12 months of deteriorating vision. She has a medical history of type 2 diabetes mellitus managed with glimepiride and hypertension managed with ramipril. Her best corrected visual acuity is 6/48 in the right eye and 6/36 in the left eye. Fundoscopy shows the presence of yellow deposits under the retina (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Central retinal artery occlusion","Optic atrophy","Optic neuritis","Macular degeneration","Diabetic retinopathy"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFundoscopy shows the presence of drusen, which are small yellow deposits under the retina. This is consistent with age-related \u003Cstrong\u003Emacular degeneration\u003C/strong\u003E. Further evaluation may involve the use of the Amsler grid.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECentral retinal artery occlusion\u003C/strong\u003E will present with sudden onset of painless loss of vision, and fundus examination will show retinal pallor and a \u0027cherry red\u0027 spot at the macula.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOptic atrophy\u003C/strong\u003E refers to death of the retinal ganglion cells, and fundus exam will show a pale optic disc. Optic atrophy and chronic papilloedema may be secondary to any condition causing stress on retinal ganglion cells, including glaucoma, optic neuritis, and papilloedema.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOptic neuritis\u003C/strong\u003E will present with painful blurring of vision associated on examination with a relative afferent pupillary defect, abnormal colour vision, and a swollen optic disc.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetic retinopathy\u003C/strong\u003E can also cause bilateral, subacute vision changes. Fundus examination will, however, show evidence of microaneurysms, hard exudates, cotton wool spots, and potential neovascularisation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A history of subacute vision changes and yellow drusen under the retina supports a diagnosis of age-related macular degeneration.","Age-related macular degeneration is a leading cause of vision loss in older adults.","Fundoscopic examination is crucial in differentiating between various causes of vision loss."],"references":["Bowling, B. (2015). Kanski\u2019s clinical ophthalmology (8th ed.). W B Saunders.","Fleckenstein M, Keenan TDL, Guymer RH, Chakravarthy U, Schmitz-Valckenberg S, Klaver CC, Wong WT, Chew EY. Age-related macular degeneration. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2021 May 6;7(1):31. doi: 10.1038/s41572-021-00265-2. PMID: 33958600. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33958600/","Ruia S, Kaufman EJ. Macular Degeneration. [Updated 2023 Jul 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK560778/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70869"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"499"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18411"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18411","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18411"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/15c4c388-5d8a-48c6-8aa6-8309ac59fa4b.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/15c4c388-5d8a-48c6-8aa6-8309ac59fa4b.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":437}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"70869","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/70869"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-22T15:12:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-22T15:14:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"499"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"86587"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"8","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/8"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc41","name":"Ophthalmology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedA